        .query { font-family: monospace; background: #f0f0f0; padding: 5px; }
        .error { color: red; }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>SQL Injection Demo</h1>
        <p>This demo simulates a product database with two modes: Vulnerable (string concatenation) and Safe (parameterized queries). Try inputs like "Laptop" or injection attempts like "' OR '1'='1" to see the difference.</p>

        <div class="mode-selection">
            <label><input type="radio" name="mode" value="vulnerable" checked> Vulnerable (Concatenation)</label>
            <label><input type="radio" name="mode" value="safe"> Safe (Parameterized)</label>
        </div>

        <div class="input-group">
            <label for="searchInput">Enter product name to search:</label>
            <input type="text" id="searchInput" placeholder="e.g., Laptop or ' OR '1'='1">
            <button id="searchButton">Search</button>
        </div>

        <div id="output" class="results">
            <h3>Generated Query:</h3>
